{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772568073,"nonce":"F5bWtAdQTAeG1kXa7mQ962MzHA4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vhMLL","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/342","origin":"github"},"title":"Streamline lint compliance workflow for project repos","message":"## Context\n\nAdding ament linter tests to project repos is a key part of the package quality\nimprovement process (#234). After completing lint fixes on `marine_ais_tools`\n(rolker/marine_ais#4), several friction points emerged that will recur across every\nrepo we onboard. This issue captures those pain points and explores solutions.\n\n## Friction observed\n\n### 1. ament_copyright header format is undocumented\nament_copyright uses substring matching against template files to identify license\ntypes. The BSD-3-Clause template requires asterisk bullets (`*`), but many existing\nfiles use numbered lists (`1.`, `2.`, `3.`). The only way to discover this was\nreading the ament_copyright source code and its template files. Result: multiple\ntest-fix-retest cycles.\n\n### 2. ament_flake8 configuration is hidden\nament_flake8 uses `max-line-length = 99`, `import-order-style = google`, and a\nspecific `extend-ignore` list — but this is buried in an ini file inside the ROS\ninstall (`/opt/ros/jazzy/lib/.../ament_flake8/configuration/ament_flake8.ini`).\nRunning `flake8` directly or `autopep8` with default settings produces wrong results.\n\n### 3. No fast feedback loop\nThe only way to check compliance is `colcon test`, which is slow. Running the ament\ntools directly (e.g., `ament_flake8`, `ament_copyright`) is faster but requires\nknowing they exist and how to invoke them.\n\n### 4. Initial bulk fix is painful\nThe first pass on a non-compliant repo requires running multiple tools in sequence\n(autopep8, isort, quote fixes, copyright header insertion) with the correct ament-\ncompatible settings. Each tool addresses a different category of violation.\n\n### 5. No regression prevention\nAfter fixing a repo, nothing prevents new violations from being introduced until\nthe next `colcon test` run.\n\n## Possible solutions to explore\n\n### Pre-commit hooks in project repos\nAdd `.pre-commit-config.yaml` to each repo with hooks that match ament's\nexpectations (autopep8/flake8 with ament settings, isort with google profile,\ncopyright checks). Benefits:\n- Auto-fixes formatting on commit\n- Fast feedback without `colcon test`\n- Works for anyone cloning the repo\n- Prevents regressions\n\nConsiderations:\n- Config must stay in sync with ament's settings or they'll disagree\n- Need to decide whether to reference ament's config or maintain a local copy\n- Installation: repo-local venv, pipx, or documented as optional\n\n### Agent knowledge files\nDocument the discovered ament lint conventions (config locations, header format\nrequirements, tool invocation commands) in `.agent/knowledge/` so agents don't\nrediscover them each session.\n\n### A lint-bootstrap script\nA one-time script that handles the initial bulk fix for a repo: runs autopep8\nwith correct settings, fixes imports, inserts copyright headers from a template,\nvalidates with ament tools. Could live in `.agent/scripts/`.\n\n### Copyright header template\nA ready-to-paste BSD-3-Clause header in the format ament_copyright recognizes,\nstored in `.agent/templates/`.\n\n### Direct ament tool invocation recipes\nDocument how to run `ament_flake8`, `ament_copyright`, etc. directly for fast\niteration without going through `colcon test`.\n\n## Relationship to other issues\n\n- #234 — Incremental package quality improvement (broader process)\n- #339 — Python package management policy (pip/venv/rosdep — relevant to tool installation)\n- #340 — Dev tools bootstrap (installing autopep8 and similar tools)\n\n## Desired outcome\n\nA repeatable, low-friction workflow for bringing a project repo into lint compliance\nand keeping it there. The approach should work for both agents and human developers.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}